{{Infobox journal | title = Aequationes Mathematicae | image = <!-- or |cover= --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = Aequ. Math.<!-- ISO 4 abbreviation --> | bluebook = <!-- For law journals only --> | mathscinet = Aequationes Math. | discipline = Mathematics | peer-reviewed = | language = English | editor = Zsolt Páles | publisher = [[Birkhäuser|Birkhäuser Science]] | country = | history = 1968 to present | frequency = Bimonthly | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 0001-9054 | eISSN = 1420-8903 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = https://www.springer.com/birkhauser/mathematics/journal/10 | link1 = https://link.springer.com/journal/10 | link1-name = Journal at SpringerLink | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }}
'''''Aequationes Mathematicae''''' is a [[mathematical journal]]. It is primarily devoted to [[functional equation]]s, but also publishes papers in [[dynamical system]]s, [[combinatorics]], and [[geometry]].<ref name=scimago/> As well as publishing regular journal submissions on these topics, it also regularly reports on international symposia on functional equations and produces bibliographies on the subject.<ref name=pk>{{citation|title=Functional Equations and Inequalities with Applications|series=Springer Monographs in Mathematics|first=Palaniappan|last=Kannappan|publisher=Springer Science+Business Media|year=2009|isbn=9780387894928|page=xi|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SdZoCM2OeuIC&pg=PR11}}</ref>
[[János Aczél (mathematician)|János Aczél]] founded the journal in 1968 at the [[University of Waterloo]], in part because of the long publication delays of up to four years in other journals at the time of its founding.<ref name=pk/><ref>{{citation|title=In Celebration of Canadian Scientists: A Decade of Killam Laureates|editor1-first=Geraldine A.|editor1-last=Kenney-Wallace|editor1-link=Geraldine A. Kenney-Wallace|editor2-first=Mel G.|editor2-last=MacLeod|editor3-first=Ralph G.|editor3-last=Stanton|editor3-link= Ralph Gordon Stanton |publisher=Charles Babbage Research Centre|year=1990|isbn=9780919611221|page=103}}</ref> It is currently published by [[Springer Science+Business Media]], with Zsolt Páles of the [[University of Debrecen]] as its editor in chief. János Aczél remains its honorary editor in chief.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.springer.com/birkhauser/mathematics/journal/10?detailsPage=editorialBoard|title=Editorial board|work=Aequationes Mathematicae|publisher=Springer Science+Business Media|accessdate=2017-10-08}}</ref>
{{As of|2016}} it was listed as a second-quartile mathematics journal by [[SCImago Journal Rank]].<ref name=scimago>{{citation|url=http://www.scimagojr.com/journalsearch.php?q=24573&tip=sid|title= Aequationes Mathematicae|work=Scimago Journal & Country Rank|accessdate=2017-10-08}}</ref>
