{{italictitle}} '''''Ars Combinatoria, a Canadian Journal of Combinatorics''''' is an [[English language]] research [[academic journal|journal]] in [[combinatorics]], issued in [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]], {{ISSN|0381-7032}}.
Beginning in June, 1976, two volumes were issued each year, dated June and December. Starting in 1995 three volumes were published each year. Starting in 2000 four volumes are published each year. It is published by The Charles Babbage Research Centre, Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20061002134635/http://www.combinatorics.net/journals/jhomes/ArsComb.html Journals in Combinatorics and Related Fields: Ars Combinatoria], The Combinatorics Net, retrieved 2014-04-05.</ref>
Tables of contents of the issues are available online. The journal is indexed in ''[[MathSciNet]]'' and ''[[Zentralblatt]]''. As of 2012, its [[SCImago Journal Rank]] two-year citation index (computed using the same formula as the [[impact factor]]) was 0.5.<ref>[http://www.scimagojr.com/journalsearch.php?q=25215&tip=sid Ars Combinatoria], SCImago Journal Rank, retrieved 2014-04-05.</ref>
